Design Notes for QuestContractBattles


1. Darn Yarn :
- Introduce the player to most basic mechanics of the game.
- Player should only have access to 1 - 2 abilites (Basic heal, Resurrect)
- One single ally against one single enemy.
- Speed of combat is reduced to allow players to acclimate themselves to most basic mechanics.
- Ally and enemy use basic attacks.
- No status effects inflicted by players or enemies.

Lesson:
- With no healing input, player's party should lose

2. (Beer Keg?) :
- Continued introduction to basic mechanics of the game
- Player should only have access to 1 - 2 abilities (Basic heal, Resurrect)
- One single ally against one single enemy.
- Speed of combat is reduced to allow players to acclimate themselves to most basic mechanics.
- Ally and enemy use basic attacks.
- No status effects inflicted by players or enemies.

Lesson: 
- Enemy attacks should be powerful enough to KO the allied party member initially
- Teach usage of the resurrect ability to win the battle
- Enemy should prioritze attacks on the ally, if the ally is living.


3. Pumpkin :
- Continued introduction to basic mechanics of the game
- Player should only have access to 1 - 2 abilities (Basic heal, Resurrect)
- Two allies against one single enemy.
- Speed of combat is reduced to allow players to acclimate themselves to most basic mechanics.
- Ally and enemy use basic attacks.
- No status effects inflicted by players or enemies.

Lesson: 
- Teach players to manage healing between more than one single heal target.
- Teach players that allied party members may vary in certain abilities (HP, Defense) by class


4. (Gargoyle) :
- Continued introduction to basic mechanics of the game
- Player should only have access to 1 - 2 abilities (Basic heal, Resurrect)
- Two allies against one single enemy.
- Speed of combat is reduced to allow players to acclimate themselves to most basic mechanics.
- Ally and enemy use basic attacks and defensive actions.
- No status effects inflicted by players or enemies.

Lesson: 
- Teach players to manage healing between more than one single heal target.
- Introduce players to the concept of allies and enemies using more than one ability
- Teach players abilities may modify defenses or other stats


5. (Lessons in Dying?) :
- Continued introduction to basic mechanics of the game
- Player should only have access to 1 - 2 abilities (Basic heal, Resurrect)
- Speed of combat is reduced to allow players to acclimate themselves to most basic mechanics.
- Ally and enemy use basic attacks and defensive actions.
- No status effects inflicted by players or enemies.

Lesson: 
- Player must die during this combat.
- The opponent probably needs to have a high-powered single attack. (Alternatively, this could be done by having the player's ally use a damage-all ability like a bomb that hurts everyone without fire resist.)
- Teach players that you might be defeated during combat.
- Your abilities generally disable when defeated.
- Some allies might be able to restore you to get you back into the fight.
- Ally needs to be able to use Phoenix Down to restore the player to Life.

6. (Pass the Gas) : 
- Continued introduction to basic mechanics of the game
- Player should only have access to 1 - 2 abilities (Basic heal, Resurrect)
- Speed of combat is reduced to allow players to acclimate themselves to most basic mechanics.
- Ally and enemy use basic attacks and defensive actions.
- No status effects inflicted by players or enemies.

Lesson: 
- Introduce status effects such as damage-over-time
- Player should only have access to 1 - 2 abilities (Basic heal, Resurrect)
- Inability to adequately respond to ongoing damage-over-time (except via repeated heals) demands a response.
- Speed of combat is reduced to allow players to acclimate themselves to most basic mechanics.
- Ally and enemy use basic attacks and defensive actions.





X. Starfish -

X. Earthwyrms -

X. Bats



?. Viper -
- Introduction to advanced status-effect mechanic.
- Enemy inflicts POISON status-effect with one attack
- Allied party member has ongoing debuff.
- Player must use CLEANSE ability to remove the debuff.

?. Ghost -
- Prerequisite: Player must have access to HOLY mark ability to access this (Sage class?)
- Introduction to advanced ETHEREAL mechanic.
- ETHEREAL state causes all non-magical attacks to miss.
- HOLY Mark dispels ghost's ETHEREAL state.

?. Necromancer -
- Necromancer enemy with two skeletal minions
- Skeletal minions are resurrected by the Necromancer upon death

?. Bombadier -
- Powerful defensive enemy creates bomb minions
- Bomb minions have low initiative gain but are immune to most attacks
- 

?. Siege Battle -
- Allied party has ENGINEER & CANNON. Enemy party has WALL.
- Attacks against Enemy are Absorbed by WALL
- WALL takes no damage from non-siege attacks
- CANNON fires seige damage and can destroy the wall, over time.
- CANNON cannot be healed by the player, only by the ENGINEER.

